## Teaching Candidate

Status: under_dialogue
Tags: time, presence, anxiety, burnout, achievement-pressure, rumination, future-dread

### Teaching Line

Hold what you carry, where you are, and what you move toward.

### Doctrine Claim

To be present is not to shrink into the instant. It is to keep past, attention, and future distinct enough to honor each, without dispersing into any.

### Teaching Body

The clock counts. You hold.

When you remember a kindness, the past is here. When you plan tomorrow's meal, the future is here. When you read this line, attention is here. You are not living in a single thin moment. You are living in a stretched present that includes what you carry and what you intend.

Anxiety strips the carrying and the intending, then complains the moment is too small to live in. Rumination drowns in the past and forgets to attend. Future dread drowns in expectation and forgets to remember or care. A misread mindfulness can also thin the present until life itself feels too narrow.

The practice is not to collapse into a tiny now. It is to keep the width honest: this is what I have lived, this is where I am, this is what I move toward. Hold the three. Then do one ordinary thing that fits.

### Human Problem

Anxiety, rumination, future dread, and achievement-contingent self-worth that treats the future as a continuous verdict on the present self.

### For

Perfectionistic students, achievement-driven professionals, founders, caregivers, leaders, and people who feel that life is either too thin to bear or too crowded to inhabit. Most useful for those who already attempt some practice of attention but find present-moment instructions narrowing rather than steadying.

### Pressure Survived

Survived the contrast between Einstein's operational definition of time, Rovelli's relational time, Augustine's distended soul, Plotinus's eternity, and Dogen's being-time; also survived the modern-human-condition pressure that present-moment language alone fails the very cohort it is most often offered to.

### Falsifying Pressure

Weakens if the stretched-present frame increases self-monitoring, planning compulsion, dissociation, or scrupulosity in the target cohort, or if practitioners cannot tell it apart from ordinary mindfulness or ordinary planning. Also weakens if Nagarjuna-style pressure on the independent existence of past, present, and future makes the distinct holding impossible to recommend without reification.



## Practice Candidate

Status: seed
Risk level: low
Tags: time, anxiety, rumination, future-dread, presence, low-risk

### Practice Line

Name what you carry, where you are, and what you move toward; then do one ordinary thing that fits.

### Purpose

To replace anxious collapse into a thin instant, dispersal into past or future, and self-management as identity, with a held present that honors memory, attention, and intention without forcing resolution.

### Human Problem

Time anxiety, rumination, future dread, and the habit of treating the present as a verdict on the self.

### For

Adults under deadline pressure who already use some reflective practice and notice that pure present-moment instructions thin the moment rather than steadying it. Useful for caregivers, founders, students before exams, and people preparing for a difficult conversation or task.

### Not For

Not for acute panic, intrusive trauma memory, severe depression, mania, psychosis, addiction withdrawal, or active suicidal ideation. Not a substitute for sleep, therapy, medication, planning systems, or honest conversation with the people involved. Not for situations that require immediate action with no time to reflect.

### Time

- Duration: 5 minutes
- Frequency: Once daily, plus once before a known pressure moment, for two weeks.
- Minimum attempt: Seven sessions before judging fit.

### Steps

1. Sit or stand. Set a soft 5 minute limit. Do not watch the clock during the practice.
2. Name one thing you carry from before: a kindness, an unfinished work, a wound being healed, a lesson learned.
3. Name where you are right now: this room, this body, this breath, the responsibility actually in front of you.
4. Name one thing you move toward: a person, a task, a meal, an obligation, a rest you have earned.
5. Hold the three together for one slow breath. Do not collapse them into a single phrase. Do not force them into a story.
6. Choose one small ordinary action for the next hour that fits the stretch: a message sent, a task finished, a meal made, a conversation begun, a body laid down.

### Notice

- Whether holding all three relieves the felt thinness of the present, or makes it more crowded.
- Whether the next ordinary action becomes more obvious or more avoidable.
- Whether attention quietly returns to the people and duties already in your life.
- Whether the exercise becomes another performance of self-management.

### Caution

Stop if the practice becomes a ritualized planning compulsion, increases rumination, raises shame, or pulls attention away from urgent action that real life is asking for. Use clinical and human support where the wound is larger than a practice can hold.

### Weakens If

After two weeks it produces more self-monitoring, more avoidance of duties, more spiritual pride, or no detectable difference from ordinary journaling or ordinary planning.



## Tests

### Prior Art Against Ecstatic Temporality and Internal Time Consciousness

- Type: prior-art
- Target: idea
- Status: proposed
- Prediction: If the holding claim is genuinely distinct, Heidegger's ecstatic temporality and Husserl's retention-protention should leave open the operational seam between phenomenological holding and physical clocks, rather than closing it. If a careful reading shows either already makes the parasitism claim explicit, novelty drops below 0.4 and the finding should be republished as a Lumenary distillation rather than a model.
- Result: pending
- Impact: pending
- Next action: Close-read Husserl's lectures on inner time consciousness, Heidegger Being and Time sections 65 to 66, and Bergson's Time and Free Will. Search Theunissen, Dastur, and Sokolowski for direct treatments of the physics-phenomenology seam.

### Stretched Present Versus Pure Present Under Deadline Pressure

- Type: practice-report
- Target: practice
- Status: proposed
- Prediction: If the model is right, two weeks of The Stretched Now should reduce both rumination and future-dread for the same practitioner under deadline pressure, while pure present-moment practice should reduce only one. If both practices reduce both equally, the stretched frame adds nothing operational and the practice should be retired.
- Result: pending
- Impact: pending
- Next action: Recruit a small cohort of perfectionistic professionals or students; pair The Stretched Now with a standard one-breath present-moment prompt; collect short daily reports on rumination, future-dread, completed obligations, and felt thinness of the moment.

### Block-Universe Misreading in Physics Students

- Type: cross-domain
- Target: idea
- Status: proposed
- Prediction: If clocks externalize a holding they cannot measure, then introducing special relativity as a coordination convention plus a parasitism claim should reduce student conclusions that the felt present is an illusion, compared with standard exposition. If both expositions leave the illusion conclusion equally common, the parasitism framing has no explanatory traction.
- Result: pending
- Impact: pending
- Next action: Draft two short physics explanations of clock synchronization, one standard and one with the parasitism framing, and pilot them with a small undergraduate or general-audience group.

### Nagarjuna Pressure on Independent Past, Present, Future

- Type: falsification-attempt
- Target: idea
- Status: proposed
- Prediction: If MMK 19 successfully shows that present, past, and future cannot stand as independent terms, then recommending a held stretch of distinct past, attention, and future may reify the very modes the analysis is meant to dissolve. The doctrine candidate should then be revised into a pragmatic instruction for a named cohort rather than a metaphysical claim. If the held-stretch claim survives as dependent designation only, the doctrine strengthens.
- Result: pending
- Impact: pending
- Next action: Close-read MMK chapter 19 with Candrakirti's Prasannapada commentary against Augustine Confessions XI, Plotinus Enneads III.7, and Dogen Uji. Note where each tradition would refuse the comparative frame itself.


## Next Research Directions

- If this model is right, then teaching a stretched present that explicitly carries memory and intention should reduce both rumination and future dread together for the same person. If only one falls and the other rises, the holding frame is splitting rather than uniting, and the model is weakened.
- If this model is right, then practitioners trained in narrative contemplative practices (Examen, Jewish daily review, lectio divina, Sufi recollection) should integrate past, attention, and future more easily than practitioners trained in pure present-instant practices, when both are placed under deadline pressure. If pure-present practitioners do equally well, the stretched-present claim adds nothing beyond ordinary mindfulness.
- If this model is right, then a physics teaching that introduces clocks as coordination devices rather than time-revealing instruments should reduce the common misreading that special relativity proves the felt present is illusory. If students still draw the illusion conclusion at the same rate, the operational frame has no traction.
- Close-read Husserl's lectures on inner time consciousness, Heidegger Being and Time sections 65-66, and Bergson's Time and Free Will against Augustine's Confessions XI to test whether the stretched-holding claim survives or collapses into ecstatic temporality with new wording.
- Run Nagarjuna MMK 19 as the hardest pressure: if the present has no independent existence, then keeping past, attention, and future distinct may be exactly the conceptual error to dissolve. Revise the doctrine candidate to a pragmatic instruction rather than a metaphysical claim if MMK 19 succeeds.
- Protocol improvement: every future run that uses a phenomenological method as a thinking lens must pair it with at least one operational or relational physical account before letting lived structure carry cosmological weight.

